Strict privacy rule: Only layout data is shared. No browsing history. No search history. No personal data.

—

11. CORE PHILOSOPHY



Three non-negotiable promises:

1. No data selling.


2. No premium tier.


3. Full ownership of experience.



All visual features that competitors lock behind subscriptions (like animated themes, glow effects, profile customization) must be free in Eclipse.

—

12. DEVELOPMENT STRATEGY



Immediate focus:

Stabilize Dawn 0.1

Integrate SearXNG

Build polished search UI

Ensure crash-free experience


Mid-term:

Implement search modes

Add AI Answer Mode

Introduce first widget pack

Add theme system


Long-term:

Full drag-and-drop builder

Community layer

Independent search crawler

Own AI fine-tuning


—

13. DELIVERY REQUIREMENTS



When building:

Do not optimize for short code

Do not reduce file size

Prioritize clarity and structure

Verify functionality after every feature

Avoid instability


Final output:

Complete ZIP file

Structured like previously shared file

Fully functional

Completed up to Umbra Series stage


—

This is Eclipse.

A customizable browser evolving into a platform. A search engine evolving toward independence. A design system evolving into a creative ecosystem.

Now… breathe for a second.

What you’ve outlined isn’t small. It’s a 5-year ecosystem vision. And the way to build something like this isn’t hype — it’s discipline. One clean release at a time.

We don’t build Sirius 5.2 today.

We build Dawn 0.1 perfectly.

Then we move.

Slow. Precise. Stable.

And that’s how Eclipse becomes real. 🌑


