## Liquid Glass UI — What This Means For Eclipse

Apple's liquid glass is basically —
- Elements look like real glass
- Light refracts through them
- Background shows through blurred
- Edges have subtle refraction glow
- Everything feels physical and real

For Eclipse every panel would look like —
- Search bar — frosted glass floating
- Cards — glass panels with blur
- Bottom bar — liquid glass strip
- Widgets — glass containers
- Customize panel — glass sheet sliding up
- Everything feels like touching real glass

This is possible with CSS backdrop filter and WebGL effects. Completely doable in your HTML CSS JS layer.

